Text.string: Vault Hunter. There's this Quinn bloke—scientist, owes us some fancy nerd tech—but we haven't heard from him in a while. Go make sure he's not dead, all right?
Lorelei? Oh, yes, uh, the Atlas lady! With the guns, and the hair—okay, I'm comin' out.
Quinn! Good to hear from you! I see the data coming in.
Data transfer in progress! Hold them off!
Got it! Thanks, Quinn! We owe you one.
Vault Hunter. Please, take one of these grenade mods as my way of saying, eh... you know... thanks for keeping me alive. It will hack any NOG so they become your temporary NOGador ally.
You can't catch me!
You'll never take me alive!
Won't stop. Can't stop. Run!

Let me explain how NOGs work. You see, their helmets project an augmented reality game over the real world. So these brainwashed idiots actually think they're playing a video game! We can hijack the game system to show their allies as enemies!
All I have to do is reprogram the NOGs' enemy identification protocols, causing them to target Maliwan instead of us! Now, I'll just prepare the NOG delivery system...
Now... this way, please!
Heh-heh, uh, about that, uh... Listen, I CERTAINLY haven't been pit-fighting reprogrammed NOGs for the locals to bet on, heh... Certainly not.
Now, use the button there to call the first NOGador into the ring.
I call him “El Fuego”! A NOG enhanced with the power of FIRE! Everyone likes fire, right?
If intel says that scientist is here, then he's here! Keep searching!

The vehicle is equipped with special, uh... “science barrels” which will send my escaped NOGs back to me through complicated digistruct technology. Technology which I don't have time to explain to you.
Ohhhh, that's not... supposed to happen. The special upgrade must have malfunctioned... But it's okay! We've got two more. Call in the next one.
That's one test NOG! A good start.

Now, I don't imagine you know anything about anything, so let me explain. The NOGs' helmets project an augmented reality game over the real world. So these little idiots think they're playing a video game, but they're actually murdering, like, hundreds of people!||Isn't that hilarious?!
Two down! One to go!
That's all of them! I will now hack into their suits and add some special upgrades of my own design to create my fighting NOGadors! I'll be waiting for you at my console whenever you're ready.
This one, I'll call “The Conductor”! Powerful as a raging lightning storm!
Oh, boy. So, uh... that didn't work either. But I can fix this! Let me just, uh... one second... no fancy gimmicks this time... Okay! Now, call the last one!
I shall call him... “NOGador Maximo”! Here's hoping we don't lose this one, too. Checking systems...
With those Maliwan boys looking for him, I'll bet Quinn's hiding in his panic room. Check it out.
Ha-HA! The hacking worked perfectly this time! The NOG will now target his own allies!
Lorelei! I'm sending you the digistruct blueprints now!
The data is uploading! Quite slowly. Keep fighting!
Just keep them off me! I need a little more time!
Yes, yes you do.

Well, it would appear our business is concluded, and, uh, my verifiable genius status is beyond question. As for me, I'll be continuing my NOG reprogramming efforts. The locals need SOMETHING to bet on, after all! [awkward laugh] Uh, I mean, uh... for the war effort, and whatnot. Yes.||Please leave now.
And just in time, too! That's the proximity alarm! Maliwan is coming after me again. Hold them off while I send the weapon plans to Lorelei!
I just need to run a few more tests on my NOG subjects, and the NOG-hacking grenade will be ready to go!
The transfer is complete! Lorelei, the blueprints for the NOG-hacking grenade are all yours!
Luckily, I have a backup plan. But I'll need your help. I'm digistructing a unique vehicle nearby. Go get it.
No, no! Don't run over them, HIT THEM! With the science barrels! I can't run my tests on dead NOGs!
Stop killing the NOGs! Hit them with the barrels!
You need to use the barrels on my escaped NOGs!
Not like that! Just a little love tap with the barrel, okay?
What are you doing?! We need those NOGs alive! Use the barrels!
Stop shooting them! We need them alive! Use the barrels!
No, no, don't shoot them! Hit them with the science barrels!
Not like that! Just... hit them with the barrels!
Lost the vehicle, did you? Okay. I'll make you a new one.
Ugh. Fine. I'll make you ANOTHER special vehicle.
I'll digistruct a new one for you, just—try not to get this one blown up, okay?
Yes, yes, all right, I'm creating a new vehicle for you.
And either way, try to get me the digistruct plans for this NOG-hacking thing he's been working on. It would really help us out if we could turn those little bastards to our side.
Ah, crap! Vault Hunter contact! High-priority target!
I, uh, sure hope someone comes along that doesn't want to shoot me in the head.
It's quiet. Too quiet.||Well, it was. Before I started talking to myself.
Guess I'll just keep hiding in here. Forever. Until I starve to death.
Huh. “Panic room”. Aptly named!
Go away, you Maliwan bastards! I am perfectly happy sitting in this closet forever. With the ratch feces and... whatever that is, ghuhghgh!
Yes, yes. I—I promised Lorelei an incredible weapon that only I, a verifiable genius, could create: a NOG-hacking grenade. Heh! That's why Maliwan's after me.
What?! Where are my NOGs?! They must have escaped during the fight. If I'm going to finish this weapon, I'll need them back.
You'll need that special vehicle to retrieve my NOGs.
Go on, then. Get to the vehicle I made for you.
Do I have to spell it out for you again? Get to the vehicle.
I told you, go pick up that vehicle.
Quinn, it's all right. Lorelei sent me to check on you.
Quinn? Lorelei instructed me to keep you alive.
Oi! Science fella—uh, Quinn. Lorelei sent me.
Hey, Quinn? Lorelei sent me to make sure you weren't dead.
IT'S TIME TO PLACE YOUR BETS, FIGHT FANS! LET'S GET—||[hacking cough]
